docs.abstract: The family of the singing star, who died seven years ago, has reached a deal with the marketing company behind the posthumous resurgence of Bob Marley.
docs.snippet: The family of the singing star, who died seven years ago, has reached a deal with the marketing company behind the posthumous resurgence of Bob Marley.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since Whitney Houston died in 2012, her estate has been pitched every kind of entertainment deal, from jukebox musicals to a traveling museum.

headline.main: Whitney Houston’s Estate Plans a Hologram Tour and a New Album
headline.print_headline: The Brand Of a Legend Comes Alive

docs.abstract: Ajit Pai said the companies had secured his support by making what he called “significant commitments” to expand rural broadband service, build a robust 5G network and sell off Boost Mobile.
docs.snippet: Ajit Pai said the companies had secured his support by making what he called “significant commitments” to expand rural broadband service, build a robust 5G network and sell off Boost Mobile.
docs.lead_paragraph: T-Mobile and Sprint moved a step closer on Monday to completing their long-sought merger, securing the public support of the Federal Communications Commission’s chairman for a deal that would reshape the country’s wireless industry.

headline.main: T-Mobile-Sprint Merger Wins Approval of F.C.C. Chairman

docs.abstract: Another Democratic town hall event on the channel liberals love to hate drew sizable ratings — and underscored the split between its news and opinion sides.
docs.snippet: Another Democratic town hall event on the channel liberals love to hate drew sizable ratings — and underscored the split between its news and opinion sides.
docs.lead_paragraph: The night began with a campaign-style biographical video and ended with a standing ovation. The candidate called President Trump’s behavior “grotesque” and lamented the “media noise machine on the right wing.” He attacked Tucker Carlson and Laura Ingraham by name.

headline.main: Fox News Welcomes Pete Buttigieg. Trump and ‘Fox & Friends’ Aren’t Pleased.
headline.print_headline: Buttigieg’s Visit Reveals Rifts Within Fox

docs.abstract: The agency’s chairman proposed a rule that would empower mobile phone carriers to automatically block the unwanted calls.
docs.snippet: The agency’s chairman proposed a rule that would empower mobile phone carriers to automatically block the unwanted calls.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The chairman of the Federal Communications Commission has repeatedly said that ending the scourge of robocalls is a top priority. On Wednesday, he announced plans for the most aggressive action yet toward achieving that goal.

headline.main: F.C.C. Moves to Increase the Use of Technology for Blocking Robocalls

docs.abstract: At the gathering after the presentation at Carnegie Hall, well-wishers lined up to greet the head of CBS’s parent company, who hadn’t attended in years.
docs.snippet: At the gathering after the presentation at Carnegie Hall, well-wishers lined up to greet the head of CBS’s parent company, who hadn’t attended in years.
docs.lead_paragraph: The TV industry is unveiling its coming season to advertisers in Manhattan this week at a series of events known as the upfronts. Three New York Times media reporters — John Koblin, Edmund Lee and Michael M. Grynbaum — assess the CBS presentation at Carnegie Hall on Wednesday.

headline.main: Shari Redstone Was the Surprise Star of the CBS Party at the Plaza
headline.print_headline: Impressions of the Upfronts for CBS, a Network in Flux

byline.original: By John Koblin, Edmund Lee and Michael M. Grynbaum

docs.abstract: The successful initial public offering by the rising coffee company bucks the recent trend of weakness among tech start-ups in China.
docs.snippet: The successful initial public offering by the rising coffee company bucks the recent trend of weakness among tech start-ups in China.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Here’s one way to compete with Starbucks in coffee: Pay your customers.

headline.main: Luckin Coffee, Chinese Rival to Starbucks, Jumps in Its U.S. Trading Debut
headline.print_headline: Java Upstart Jolts Tech In Hot I.P.O.

docs.abstract: Viewers are fleeing for Netflix. The ones who stay are older than the group prized by advertisers. Here’s a look back at the troubled 2018-19 season.
docs.snippet: Viewers are fleeing for Netflix. The ones who stay are older than the group prized by advertisers. Here’s a look back at the troubled 2018-19 season.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the curtain comes down on the 2018-19 television season, the major broadcast networks found themselves sinking deeper into trouble.

headline.main: Running Scared: Network TV in the Streaming Age

docs.abstract: Several officials expressed concern that low inflation could become permanent, hamstringing the Fed’s room to cut interest rates next time the economy weakens.
docs.snippet: Several officials expressed concern that low inflation could become permanent, hamstringing the Fed’s room to cut interest rates next time the economy weakens.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal Reserve officials are increasingly worried that inflation is too low and could leave the central bank with less room to maneuver in an economic downturn.

headline.main: Fed Officials Sound an Alarm, Worrying Weak Inflation Could Last
headline.print_headline: Fed Officials Sound Alarm Over Stubbornly Weak Inflation

docs.abstract: Uber’s offering was supposed to be a crowning moment for the ride-hailing company. But it suffered setback after setback and ultimately resulted in pointed questions for all involved.
docs.snippet: Uber’s offering was supposed to be a crowning moment for the ride-hailing company. But it suffered setback after setback and ultimately resulted in pointed questions for all involved.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last September, Uber’s top executives were pitched by some of Wall Street’s biggest banks, Morgan Stanley and Goldman Sachs.

headline.main: How the Promise of a $120 Billion Uber I.P.O. Evaporated
headline.print_headline: How Enthusiasm for Uber Evaporated Before I.P.O.

docs.abstract: While technology like 3-D printing makes car collecting less expensive and more accessible, it has also made it harder to determine the actual value of a car.
docs.snippet: While technology like 3-D printing makes car collecting less expensive and more accessible, it has also made it harder to determine the actual value of a car.
docs.lead_paragraph: Need a part for a 1964 Mustang? Online catalogs offer a heater knob, a complete unibody or anything in between. With easily found replica components, you could effectively build a new ’64 from the tires up.

headline.main: New Parts for Old Cars May Keep Them Running, but Sink Their Value
headline.print_headline: Just Like New, and That’s the Problem
